<author><name><![CDATA[nemos]]></name></author>
<updated>2013-03-25T15:41:21-07:00</updated>
<published>2013-03-25T15:41:21-07:00</published>
<id>http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=433&amp;p=2233#p2233</id>
<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=433&amp;p=2233#p2233"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Item selection in Windows Explorer]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=433&amp;p=2233#p2233"><![CDATA[
(...I don't know if it is another Win7 &quot;feature&quot; or a side-effect of Classic Shell...)<br /><br />Take the following steps (forget your mouse; use only the keyboard):<br />- Open Windows Explorer with WinButton+E keyboard shortcut.<br />- Navigate to any folder<strong> <span style="color:#ff0000;">in the right pane</span></strong>.<br />- Check any item <strong><span style="color:#ff0000;">in the right pane</span></strong>; leave it highlighted.<br />- Press Tab about 4 times until you highlight the parent folder <strong><span style="color:#0000ff;">in the left pane</span></strong>.<br />The item selection in the right pane looks active, but it is not; the active selection is in the left pane...<br /><br />So, if you marked a single file in the right pane e.g. for deletion (and you are a tired enough), it is possible to delete the entire directory from the left pane!<br /><br />(...I was lucky enough to find the folder in the Recycle Bin...)<br /><br />Any ideas?<br /><br /><em><span style="color:#800080;">[edit]</span></em><br />...And if you bring another window in the foreground and then revert to Windows Explorer, even the dotted frame from the left pane selection disappears!!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=299">nemos</a> — Mon Mar 25, 2013 3:41 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
